title: For Sale/Trade:  DON'T GET RIPPED OFF BY THE SHARKS!!!
postcontent:
You might have noticed, after reports became public that the ATF is currently reviewing a ban on 5.56x45 XM855 commonly known as "green tip" ammunition, it became hard to find it at any retailer in store and online.  

What's even more noticeable is the worthless trash on this website and others that have immediately begun exploiting this circumstance by offering this ammunition for sale at ridiculous prices.  

What's more amusing, is the level of ignorance that is being spewed by these people about this ammunition and what the ATF is going and not going to do.  Playing on people's emotions and spreading misinformation. 

So, before you fall pray to this trash type seller/exploiter, before you throw your hard earned money away to line their pockets, take a few minutes and finish reading this post, you'll save yourself a great deal of money, but more importantly, you won't get RIPPED OFF...

FACTS:

The ATF is currently reviewing a ban on XM855, however it is also reviewing a ban on 39 other classes of ammunition and has been for years.  Those classes of ammunition have been selling just the same since their own ban review began even years ago.

The last time the ATF was actually successful in banning a class of ammunition was back in 1993.  That ban was for Teflon coated ammunition that was designed to penetrate Kevlar vests.  That type of ammunition was commonly known as "cop killer" ammunition. 

The actual ban process on a class of ammunition is not as easy as it sounds.  Often times it takes years and the ATF has an uphill battle in most cases tied up in court by groups and organizations like the NRA fighting them tooth and nail.  So if you want to spend your money wisely, become a member of the NRA or if you're already a member, send them a donation.  They and other organizations like them are the only thing standing between us and government overreach.  

As the current frenzy on this ammunition is subsiding, retailers are beginning to have XM855 available and in stock again.  Examples are Palmetto State Armory and Gander mountain, they have it in stock, Midway and Cabela's expect to have it by the weekend.  They are charging normal prices for it.

In closing, THANK YOU for taking the time to read this post, I hope I've succeeded in preventing you from wasting your money.  As you can see, I have no vested interest in leading or misleading you in any direction, nor am I attempting to sell you anything.  I do ask that if you like this post, send me a quick note.  

Happy Hunting...

title: For Sale:  I do Glock/Others Trigger & Action Jobs. Polished Internals, Barrel Refinish, Custom Parts Install, etc.
postcontent:
Offering Glock Frame and Slide Internal parts Polishing, Worn Barrel Refinishing, Custom Parts Install(Sights, Triggers, ANY PART).....I have 3.5lb connectors and 6lb trigger springs on hand, but I can do what ever weight you want, just request it and I'll get it.......I also do other guns! 
Please Read


 Who Am I:
 My names Chris. I have done countless Glock Trigger/Slide jobs on my own Glocks as well as many others people Glocks. I also do other weapons including Handguns and Rifles. I am legally allowed to possess a Handgun, I can show you my CCP and Mil ID so you know I'm not a felon. I do not own a shop, I do this as a hobby and to help people with cost. I will however do the same if not better job then you will get at a gunshop for a fraction of the price, you can pay over $100 for a polish job at gunshops! I enjoy gunwork and I do this as a hobby, I have been for many years and I am very familiar with Glocks and many others, just shoot me a message with what gun you have.  Turnaround is 48hrs, however in most cases it is ready for pickup next day, I say 48hrs for a 1 day buffer in case I have something going on with work. Cant beat that! Also I can install what ever custom parts you have purchased on your own. There will be a "Pre" and "Post" work form to fill out stating what services will be provided and that your giving and taking back possession. A copy will be made for you to keep.
 -------------------------------------------------
 Why Polish Internals?:
 Polishing is like waxing a floor. Less friction equals smoother surface, which in our case equals a physically smoother operating gun and a smoother feel to the user. Glocks come stock with a 5lb trigger pull which in reality is closer to 6lb, sometimes slightly more, due to all the friction from factory coated parts. Polishing will bring it to where it should be with stock parts which is roughly 4.5lbs-5lbs, thus making the trigger pull feel lighter then your used to. I also offer two parts to further reduce trigger pull and enhance smoothness, that when coupled with the polish job will make your Glock operate as smooth as possible and make the trigger pull break like glass every time....Pull the trigger on one of my glocks before you commit and see for yourself!
 -------------------------------------------------
 What I offer:
 I will completely disassemble the gun(slide and frame), clean the entire gun(bore at your request), polish all friction prone internals, oil and reassemble. Can also polish Barrel Feed Ramp at your request with no additional Fee.
 Price $25

 I will Remove the Factory 5lb Connector and replace it with a POLISHED 3.5lb connector. This reduces the trigger pull to roughly 3lbs-3.5lbs.
 Price $15

 I will Remove the Factory 5lb Trigger Spring and Replace it with a 6lb Trigger Spring. Why heavier here? The Trigger Spring actually assists the Trigger in Pull/Reset, a Heavier one will make for a Smoother pull and Smoother Reset.
 Price $5

 I will refinish your scratched/worn barrel by slightly sanding, degreasing and applying an even coat of Black DuraCoat DuraBake which is a heat treated form of Duracoat making it hard as nails once its heated.
 $15

For any custom parts you would like installed, please let me know and I will give you a quote. I can install parts you bought or I can order them for you at a discounted rate and save you some money.
 -------------------------------------------------
 Turnaround is 48hrs, however in most cases it is ready for pickup next day, I say 48hrs for a 1 day buffer in case I have something going on with work. Cant beat that! Also I can install what ever custom parts you have purchased on your own. There will be a "Pre" and "Post" work form to fill out stating what services will be provided and that your giving and taking back possession. A copy will be made for you to keep.

 Feel free to contact me to setup a time, thanks.
 Chris
